{
  "suite": "countif_kana_folding_probes",
  "description": "Mac Excel ja-JP COUNTIF text-equality folds certain Japanese character classes onto a canonical form before comparing. The two existing divergences (countif_jp_katakana_vs_hiragana, countif_fullwidth_star_literal) pin two specific behaviours but do not delineate the full extent of the folding. These probes map out the boundaries — hiragana/katakana, half-width/full-width katakana, full-width punctuation, full-width digits, voiced-mark normalisation — before designing the criteria.cpp matcher fix.\n",
  "environment": {
    "excel_version": "16.108.1",
    "excel_locale": "ja-JP",
    "date1904": false,
    "iterative": false,
    "generated_at": "2026-04-26T21:07:16Z"
  },
